SORT: common sorting algorithms in C
====================================

COMPILE:
    make
        -> generates <libsort.a>
    make clean
        -> cleans up all generated files

USAGE:
    1) compile
    2) add <libsort.a> to CWD
    3) #include "sort.h"
    4) add <-L. -lsort> in gcc

METHODS:
    void selectionSort(int arr[], int n);
    void bubbleSort(int arr[], int n);
    void insertionSort(int arr[], int n);
    void quickSort(int arr[], int n);
    void mergeSort(int arr[], int n);

TESTING:
    a tester file is provided for your
    convenience:
        make
        gcc tester.c -L. -lsort -o tester
        ./tester